Subject: Re: all/7776: DrScheme/Debugger move buttons to right to increase
 result display area.
Date: Mon, 26 Dec 2005 13:02:12 -0500

 As a further thought, I wonder if it may be worth while removing the default
 Analyze button/functionality from the build, and placing the debugger
 buttons on the first row with the other buttons, leaving the second text row
 exposed when debugging entirely for debug text output.
 
 - where by default the present value at the step location is displayed as is
 presently done.
 
 - but when the cursor is moved over a specific variable or primitive
 (non-mutating) function, it's evaluated value is displayed in place of the
 default evaluation value above. (as it would be nice for example to be able
 to see the interactive result of an arbitrary in-scope (car x) not just x,
 but of course it wouldn't likely be a good idea to evaluate a port function
 if it destructively altered it's state (although would be cute to be able to
 peek).
 
 
 
